                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/soci-377" class="program-course-title">
              SOCI 377 Deviance (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-35617" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Sociology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Sociology (Arts)              : Introduction to the sociological study of deviance. Emphasis on the "societal reaction" or "interactionist" approach to deviance. The correctional and causal approach towards deviance, its limitations and alternative ways to address the subject of deviance.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Eran Shor (Fall)                  </p>

    
      </div>

