                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/soci-388" class="program-course-title">
              SOCI 388 Crime (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-35623" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Sociology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Sociology (Arts)              : Introductory course on methods and theories in criminology. Exploration of the nature and distribution of crime; and critical evaluation of definitions and the measurement of crime; review of theoretical approaches used to understand such a phenomenon; a comparative overview of the criminal justice system.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
