                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/soci-495" class="program-course-title">
              SOCI 495 Social Problems and Conflicts (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-35665" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Sociology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Sociology (Arts)              : This course explores the social construction of "social problems". It focuses on the social conflicts involved in the definition of social issues and on how and why "problems" change over time. Issues such as drinking, smoking, drug use, pornography, abortion, and homosexuality will be discussed.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Eran Shor (Winter)                  </p>

    
